    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Trichotosia buruensis are tincture, infusion, tea, decoction, and salve. Tincture is made by soaking the plant in a solvent such as ethanol to extract its bioactive compounds, while infusion and tea are prepared by steeping the plant material in hot water. Decoction is a process of boiling the plant material to extract its soluble compounds, often used for harder plant parts like bark or roots. Salve is a topical preparation made by infusing the plant material in a carrier oil to create a medicated cream or ointment. These preparations are utilized to harness the plant's purported medicinal properties, including anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial activities.",
